00:35:12,020 --> 00:35:12,780
No.

588
00:35:15,260 --> 00:35:17,060
As far as I know,

589
00:35:17,060 --> 00:35:20,140
an errand is independent.

590
00:35:20,140 --> 00:35:21,460
When it’s done, it’s done.

591
00:35:21,460 --> 00:35:24,380
It’s not the beginning or the end.

592
00:35:28,060 --> 00:35:29,580
You’re here

593
00:35:29,860 --> 00:35:31,660
for something else.

594
00:35:31,660 --> 00:35:33,340
No.

595
00:35:33,860 --> 00:35:36,060
I’ve never gone out before.

596
00:35:37,500 --> 00:35:39,940
I used to practice my skills

597
00:35:39,940 --> 00:35:41,500
at home.

598
00:35:41,500 --> 00:35:43,140
There’s no beginning or end.

599
00:35:43,700 --> 00:35:45,780
Practice your skills at home?

600
00:35:45,780 --> 00:35:47,340
And why

601
00:35:47,340 --> 00:35:49,140
do you do that?

602
00:35:49,140 --> 00:35:50,740
It’s my passion.

603
00:35:51,540 --> 00:35:54,340
Your errand is done

604
00:35:54,340 --> 00:35:55,700
and you’ve found no one,

605
00:35:55,700 --> 00:35:58,740
shouldn’t you go back
to pursue your passion?

606
00:35:58,740 --> 00:36:00,620
Why did you say

607
00:36:00,620 --> 00:36:02,820
you don’t know where to go?

608
00:36:08,580 --> 00:36:10,380
What do you

609
00:36:10,980 --> 00:36:12,700
practice those skills for?

610
00:36:13,860 --> 00:36:17,140
Why do I practice those skills?

611
00:36:18,180 --> 00:36:19,940
At first,

612
00:36:19,940 --> 00:36:22,700
that was to gain Mom’s recognition.

613
00:36:22,700 --> 00:36:24,140
And then...

614
00:36:24,140 --> 00:36:25,420
This is the first life

615
00:36:25,420 --> 00:36:27,460
the Snow-breaking Blade took

616
00:36:27,460 --> 00:36:30,340
since it reappeared.

617
00:36:30,340 --> 00:36:31,580
Even if I’m the only one left,

618
00:36:31,580 --> 00:36:32,340
I’ll escort you back

619
00:36:32,340 --> 00:36:34,260
to the Fortress.

620
00:36:39,140 --> 00:36:40,420
Right after coming out,

621
00:36:40,420 --> 00:36:43,940
when she saw Demons
attacking Huo’s Manor

622
00:36:43,940 --> 00:36:46,340
she beat them back

623
00:36:46,340 --> 00:36:48,020
on her own,

624
00:36:48,020 --> 00:36:49,820
killed Blessed Dog

625
00:36:50,120 --> 00:36:52,740
and fought her way out

626
00:36:52,740 --> 00:36:54,780
to Mount Heng.

627
00:36:54,780 --> 00:36:56,140
There,

628
00:36:56,140 --> 00:36:59,060
she lured Dragon Master out

629
00:36:59,060 --> 00:37:01,610
and killed him.

630
00:37:08,780 --> 00:37:09,900
To...

631
00:37:11,140 --> 00:37:12,740
To honor my grandfather’s blade.

632
00:37:13,940 --> 00:37:15,340
The Blades, Sword, Palm’s time

633
00:37:15,340 --> 00:37:16,780
is over.

634
00:37:17,420 --> 00:37:18,340
We, as their descendants,

635
00:37:18,340 --> 00:37:19,820
could barely

636
00:37:19,820 --> 00:37:21,820
protect ourselves

637
00:37:21,820 --> 00:37:23,740
with their weapons.

638
00:37:24,260 --> 00:37:25,940
How shameful that is!

639
00:37:25,940 --> 00:37:27,580
It shouldn’t be

640
00:37:27,580 --> 00:37:29,060
like that.

641
00:37:29,420 --> 00:37:31,140
You’re from a prominent family.

642
00:37:37,100 --> 00:37:38,340
I almost forgot

643
00:37:39,140 --> 00:37:42,020
about things at home.

644
00:37:42,820 --> 00:37:44,900
Huo Liantao is gone.

645
00:37:44,900 --> 00:37:46,100
Those thugs like Ding Kui

646
00:37:46,100 --> 00:37:47,690
would become even more unscrupulous.

647
00:37:48,660 --> 00:37:49,900
I need to go back

648
00:37:49,900 --> 00:37:52,280
and tell my mom everything.

649
00:37:53,020 --> 00:37:54,740
And that Bracelet...

650
00:38:03,660 --> 00:38:04,660
Abbot,

651
00:38:05,940 --> 00:38:06,740
could you put me

652
00:38:06,740 --> 00:38:08,860
outside Lingling?

653
00:38:10,020 --> 00:38:12,060
Go check in the cabin.

654
00:38:31,080 --> 00:38:34,920
♪So lucky to get the wooden peach
from you♪

655
00:38:35,140 --> 00:38:39,550
♪So does the hero braving the world♪

656
00:38:39,910 --> 00:38:43,410
♪Petals fly in the dream♪

657
00:38:43,970 --> 00:38:48,140
♪Like greeting the old friend♪

658
00:38:48,140 --> 00:38:55,400
♪Keep the vow we made until death♪

659
00:38:56,360 --> 00:39:00,110
♪However far to go♪

660
00:39:00,480 --> 00:39:04,000
♪However high to reach♪

661
00:39:04,650 --> 00:39:15,670
♪This moment is worth my forever love♪

662
00:39:37,100 --> 00:39:38,140
Abbot,

663
00:39:38,140 --> 00:39:40,220
can he be cured?

664
00:39:42,140 --> 00:39:43,220
I’ve given him

665
00:39:43,620 --> 00:39:46,260
acupuncture and medicine

666
00:39:46,260 --> 00:39:48,500
to prolong his life.

667
00:39:48,500 --> 00:39:52,540
As for how to remove Bone-chilling,

668
00:39:52,540 --> 00:39:54,100
we’ve been working on it

669
00:39:54,100 --> 00:39:56,280
since decades ago,

670
00:39:57,060 --> 00:39:58,500
but to no avail

671
00:39:58,500 --> 00:40:00,290
so far.

672
00:40:05,620 --> 00:40:06,620
I knew the reappearance

673
00:40:06,620 --> 00:40:09,140
of the Cloud-impelling Palm

674
00:40:09,140 --> 00:40:10,740
was a bad sign.

675
00:40:10,740 --> 00:40:12,260
So I came all the way

676
00:40:12,260 --> 00:40:13,300
but

677
00:40:13,300 --> 00:40:14,760
arrived late.

678
00:40:15,620 --> 00:40:19,060
He seems to know Xie Yun.

679
00:40:19,060 --> 00:40:21,260
Is he here especially for him?

680
00:40:22,980 --> 00:40:23,850
Abbot,

681
00:40:24,500 --> 00:40:26,700
may I ask your name?

682
00:40:29,540 --> 00:40:31,500
Finally!

683
00:40:33,420 --> 00:40:35,660
Think again.

684
00:40:35,660 --> 00:40:36,880
What else have you forgotten?

685
00:40:38,980 --> 00:40:42,660
I’m Tongming,

686
00:40:42,660 --> 00:40:43,820
a nobody drifting from place to place.

687
00:40:43,820 --> 00:40:46,820
I don’t think you’ve heard of me.

688
00:40:47,740 --> 00:40:49,380
Tongming?

689
00:40:49,380 --> 00:40:51,220
Never heard of it.

690
00:40:51,900 --> 00:40:53,560
That little rascal inside

691
00:40:54,260 --> 00:40:55,940
is my disciple.

692
00:40:57,100 --> 00:40:58,140
That said,

693
00:40:58,580 --> 00:41:00,700
unlike me,

694
00:41:00,700 --> 00:41:02,520
he isn’t a monk

695
00:41:03,100 --> 00:41:05,700
of any kind.

696
00:41:07,340 --> 00:41:10,300
He did shave his head
when he was little,

697
00:41:10,980 --> 00:41:13,620
but I knew he has burdens,

698
00:41:13,620 --> 00:41:16,020
so I didn’t convert him to Buddhism.

699
00:41:16,020 --> 00:41:17,620
Back then, nobody took him seriously.

700
00:41:17,620 --> 00:41:19,300
He was bored

701
00:41:20,220 --> 00:41:22,420
and returned to the secular world

702
00:41:22,420 --> 00:41:24,300
a few years later.

703
00:41:26,860 --> 00:41:28,140
Abbot,

704
00:41:28,460 --> 00:41:29,060
now I see

705
00:41:29,060 --> 00:41:30,180
why he’s

706
00:41:30,180 --> 00:41:31,540
such a nagger.

707
00:41:36,260 --> 00:41:38,820
Xie Yun once told me,

708
00:41:38,820 --> 00:41:40,260
thanks to his uncle,

709
00:41:40,260 --> 00:41:42,580
who transferred all his energy to him,

710
00:41:42,580 --> 00:41:44,700
he didn’t die of Bone-chilling.

711
00:41:47,620 --> 00:41:49,500
That was the only way

712
00:41:49,500 --> 00:41:52,620
to stop it from spreading.

713
00:41:52,620 --> 00:41:55,360
I gave him acupuncture
to suppress the poison.

714
00:41:56,100 --> 00:41:59,020
I knew that was only

715
00:41:59,020 --> 00:42:00,660
a temporary expedient.

716
00:42:00,660 --> 00:42:02,740
And Anzhi was born

717
00:42:02,740 --> 00:42:04,580
compassionate.

718
00:42:04,580 --> 00:42:06,340
He wouldn’t turn a blind eye

719
00:42:06,340 --> 00:42:08,500
to others’ suffering.

720
00:42:11,220 --> 00:42:12,330
Anzhi?

721
00:42:13,300 --> 00:42:15,500
That’s his courtesy name.

722
00:42:15,500 --> 00:42:16,980
Didn’t he tell you about it?

723
00:42:18,540 --> 00:42:21,540
He introduced himself as Xie Meimei.

724
00:42:22,340 --> 00:42:24,940
When the mutiny broke out,

725
00:42:24,940 --> 00:42:27,260
Anzhi was still in his infancy

726
00:42:27,260 --> 00:42:28,860
and was taken out

727
00:42:28,860 --> 00:42:30,460
by an old eunuch.

728
00:42:30,460 --> 00:42:32,020
Then we found him on the way.

729
00:42:38,860 --> 00:42:40,300
Master,

730
00:42:40,300 --> 00:42:42,540
why can’t I be a monk?

731
00:42:42,540 --> 00:42:44,180
You’re one

732
00:42:44,180 --> 00:42:46,740
and so should I.

733
00:42:48,500 --> 00:42:50,340
A monk

734
00:42:50,340 --> 00:42:52,220
has to break free from his burdens.

735
00:42:52,220 --> 00:42:53,380
Anzhi,

736
00:42:53,820 --> 00:42:56,260
do you know what burden means?

737
00:42:59,300 --> 00:43:00,500
If you ask me,

738
00:43:00,500 --> 00:43:02,020
you’re too cowardly

739
00:43:02,020 --> 00:43:03,660
to bear your burden.

740
00:43:04,260 --> 00:43:06,700
Why should I?

741
00:43:06,700 --> 00:43:09,140
I can’t choose who my father is.

742
00:43:09,140 --> 00:43:10,180
If I could,

743
00:43:10,180 --> 00:43:12,060
I wouldn’t be his son.

744
00:43:14,300 --> 00:43:16,250
Whose son would you rather be instead?

745
00:43:16,860 --> 00:43:20,780
A fisherman’s, a boatman’s, a porter’s

746
00:43:20,780 --> 00:43:22,420
and so on.

747
00:43:22,420 --> 00:43:23,980
Then I wouldn’t have to study

748
00:43:23,980 --> 00:43:25,260
or practice martial arts.

749
00:43:25,260 --> 00:43:26,620
When I grew up,

750
00:43:26,620 --> 00:43:28,860
I could still make a living

751
00:43:29,420 --> 00:43:31,180
by being a waiter or a carter.

752
00:43:31,180 --> 00:43:33,140
The former could learn
all kinds of information

753
00:43:33,140 --> 00:43:35,460
and the latter could explore the world.

754
00:43:35,460 --> 00:43:38,100
Wouldn’t that be better?

755
00:43:41,380 --> 00:43:42,940
Merciful Buddha.

756
00:43:42,940 --> 00:43:43,780
Master,

757
00:43:43,780 --> 00:43:45,540
am I wrong?

758
00:43:46,300 --> 00:43:47,100
You’ve only seen

759
00:43:47,100 --> 00:43:50,260
those kids on the beach
are living an easy life,

760
00:43:50,820 --> 00:43:51,860
but you don’t know

761
00:43:51,860 --> 00:43:52,940
that’ll only last for so long.

762
00:43:52,940 --> 00:43:54,420
The rest of their lives

763
00:43:54,420 --> 00:43:56,180
won’t be that easy.

764
00:43:57,140 --> 00:43:59,500
Once they grow up,

765
00:43:59,500 --> 00:44:01,740
they’ll start working
for their families.

766
00:44:01,740 --> 00:44:04,660
They’ll have to carry goods

767
00:44:04,660 --> 00:44:08,100
and punt boats day after day,

768
00:44:08,100 --> 00:44:10,740
working from dawn to dusk

769
00:44:10,740 --> 00:44:13,500
only to scrape by.

770
00:44:13,500 --> 00:44:16,510
They can’t afford to rest or have fun.

771
00:44:17,340 --> 00:44:20,940
Their families rely on them.

772
00:44:20,940 --> 00:44:23,220
The burden is so heavy

773
00:44:26,460 --> 00:44:29,500
that they can’t afford
to get sick or die.

774
00:44:29,500 --> 00:44:33,340
The only choice is
to bow their heads and go on.

775
00:44:33,340 --> 00:44:35,540
That’s in the good years.

776
00:44:35,540 --> 00:44:37,780
In the bad ones,

777
00:44:37,780 --> 00:44:39,540
the situation will be worse.

778
00:44:39,540 --> 00:44:43,140
Only few can survive.

779
00:44:43,140 --> 00:44:46,140
Do you know

780
00:44:46,140 --> 00:44:47,410
what are they thinking?

781
00:44:51,820 --> 00:44:53,700
Merciful Buddha.

782
00:44:56,380 --> 00:44:58,180
They’re thinking

783
00:44:58,180 --> 00:44:59,540
why

784
00:44:59,540 --> 00:45:02,380
I wasn’t born into a noble family.

785
00:45:02,900 --> 00:45:05,140
The world is even crueler to girls.

786
00:45:05,140 --> 00:45:07,500
When they are little,

787
00:45:07,500 --> 00:45:09,540
they pray not to be sold.

788
00:45:09,900 --> 00:45:12,140
When they’re married
into other families,

789
00:45:12,140 --> 00:45:15,100
they beg for their mercy.

790
00:45:15,100 --> 00:45:18,260
They can’t control their lives.

791
00:45:18,260 --> 00:45:20,260
As humans,

792
00:45:20,260 --> 00:45:22,900
they’re as helpless as farm animals.

793
00:45:24,740 --> 00:45:28,220
Do you know what are they thinking?

794
00:45:30,380 --> 00:45:31,660
Life and death

795
00:45:31,660 --> 00:45:34,140
are inevitable.

796
00:45:34,140 --> 00:45:36,140
Most people spend most of their lives

797
00:45:36,140 --> 00:45:39,540
trying to change their fate.

798
00:45:43,020 --> 00:45:45,000
But that’s not easy.

799
00:45:45,780 --> 00:45:47,860
You think your life is bitter

800
00:45:47,860 --> 00:45:51,020
because you haven’t seen the worst.

801
00:45:51,780 --> 00:45:52,820
Master,

802
00:45:52,820 --> 00:45:54,960
is there a kind of life
that’s not bitter?

803
00:46:03,090 --> 00:46:06,610
♪Stars flow like river♪

804
00:46:07,650 --> 00:46:11,250
♪My yearning falls into the river♪

805
00:46:11,810 --> 00:46:15,890
♪Now that you’re in my life♪

806
00:46:16,130 --> 00:46:19,770
♪I will never be alone♪

807
00:46:19,770 --> 00:46:23,890
♪I haven’t seen the mountains with you♪

808
00:46:24,330 --> 00:46:28,770
♪Nor have I tied up your hair♪

809
00:46:29,410 --> 00:46:33,970
♪We haven’t finished our story in chaos♪

810
00:46:34,210 --> 00:46:38,850
♪The blade hasn’t been returned♪

811
00:46:39,010 --> 00:46:42,850
♪I fear not to roam the world with you♪

812
00:46:43,090 --> 00:46:47,770
♪When I go across the world for you♪

813
00:46:48,010 --> 00:46:51,770
♪I’m willing to shed blood for you♪

814
00:46:52,090 --> 00:46:57,170
♪Don’t mind whose land it is♪

815
00:46:57,170 --> 00:47:01,130
♪Where is home to the snowflake♪

816
00:47:01,130 --> 00:47:05,650
♪Come and melt in my embrace♪

817
00:47:06,290 --> 00:47:13,370
♪The spring sun is an invisible armor
that’ll hold♪

818
00:47:14,130 --> 00:47:18,730
♪The purest love is unadorned♪
